      <hedline>
        <hl1>This Is Democracy?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ian MacKinnon letter on Herbert Muschamp's August 27 article decries current definition of public places as getting away from it all (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Herbert Muschamp's democratic space is a bank plaza where you take a ''vacation from distractions'' [''Public Space or Private, a Compulsion to Fill It,'' Aug. 27]. Our agora is so withered that public places are now defined by getting away from it all; corporate-municipal ''art'' is often to assist in the erasure of unpermitted vending, politics, begging, art and performance.</p>
        <p>IAN MACKINNON  Cambridge, Mass.</p>
      </block>
